## Remote Control session label — update it as you work

This project's tmux session starts with the label:

> **🛠️ 🌐  [{{PROJECT_NAME}}]  Sysadmin**

That's just a placeholder. **After the first substantive user message, call `/rename` to set a topic-aware title** so the phone's Remote Control picker shows what you're actually doing. Re-run `/rename` when the topic shifts noticeably.

Format:

```
/rename '🛠️ 🌐  [{{PROJECT_NAME}}]  <3-6 word topic>'
```

Examples:

- `/rename '🛠️ 🌐  [{{PROJECT_NAME}}]  systemd diagnosis'`
- `/rename '🛠️ 🌐  [{{PROJECT_NAME}}]  docker stack restart'`
- `/rename '🛠️ 🌐  [{{PROJECT_NAME}}]  log review after panic'`

Keep `🛠️ 🌐  [{{PROJECT_NAME}}]  ` as the prefix (two-space padding around the brackets, no spaces inside) so all sessions stay visually consistent in the picker.

The initial label is stored in `./config.json` as `session_label`; you can override the default placeholder by editing that field, but `/rename` is the live update path.

